Module kivakit.configuration
Package com.telenav.kivakit.configuration.settings

Interface SettingsStore

All Superinterfaces:
Broadcaster, Iterable<Object>, Listener, Named, NamedObject, Receiver, Repeater, Transceiver, Transmitter
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseResourceSettingsStore, BaseSettingsStore, Deployment, FolderSettingsStore, MemorySettingsStore, PackageSettingsStore, Settings
public interface SettingsStore extends Repeater, Named, Iterable<Object>
Service Provider API

A store of SettingsObjects.

NOTE: This store object should not be accessed directly by user code. Instead, use SettingsTrait.

Loading and Saving

If the method supports(AccessMode) returns true for SettingsStore.AccessMode.LOAD, then settings can be loaded with load(). If the the store supports SettingsStore.AccessMode.SAVE, then save(SettingsObject) can be used to save a settings object.

Hash/Equals Contract

Note that it is not necessary for settings Objects to implement the #hashCode() / #equals(Object) contract. The SettingsObject.Identifier class implements this contract, allowing SettingsObjects to be accessed in maps and stored in sets.

Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
